ADO-EKITI – The Ekiti State Police Commissioner, Babatunde Mobayo has disclosed that the command was doing everything within its powers to secure the release of the remaining kidnapped victim in Ekiti. The CP therefore implored  anyone with useful information that could expose the criminals to report to the nearest Police Station in his or her domain. Speaking through the  Police Public Relations Officer(PPRO) Sunday Abutu,the Police Chief who confirmed the abduction  of two persons on Christmas Day however said one of the victims has been rescued. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The incident occurred at Isan-Ekiti/ Iludun road same spot where former Commissioner for Agriculture in Ekiti State, Mr Folorunso Olabode, was kidnapped a few weeks back. The CP said his men at the Oye Divisional Police Station worked with other local security outfits to rescue one of the victims. Morocco, Israel To Re-Establish Regular Flights Ensuring An Indivisible Nigeria Is NAF’s Cardinal Objective “On  December 25, 2020 at about 6pm, a distress call was received by Oye DPO  that some unknown gunmen forcefully stopped one Lexus Jeep along Isan/Iludun Ekiti road and kidnapped the two occupants. “Upon receipt of the information, the DPO led his team to the scene with the assistance of the Amotekun Corps, the Vigilantes and the Hunters, one of the victims was rescued while serious effort is ongoing to ensure the rescue of the other victim.” Abutu said the success of the operation indicated the readiness of the police to work with the locals in Ekiti to rid the state of criminal elements. Meanwhile, a source told newsmen that a vehicle coming behind the victims quickly alerted the police and Amotekun corps for speedy action. “It was a vehicle coming behind the Jeep conveying the victims that stopped his car and fled into the bush to contact some people. “The people contacted immediately called the police in Oye-Ekiti and Amotekun corps who were joined by local hunters and gave the gunmen a hot chase into the bush and rescued one of the victims.” SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION